  <h3 id="tabs-fake">
    Fake Tabs
  </h3>
  <p>
    A fake tab
    <em>looks</em>
    like a normal tab, but is actually a hyperlink to a new page.
    Therefore a set of fake tabs behaves more like a simple navigational widget,
    rather than a dynamic user interface control.
  </p>
  <p>
    If HREF is not present, then the tab will be in disabled state.
    A value of "javascript" (or any such variant) is
    <strong>not</strong>
    a valid URL!
  </p>
  <p>
    The
    <code>aria-current</code>
    attribute is used to programmatically denote the current page state
    and current link.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use child element modifier
    <code>fake-tabs__items--large</code>
